javadoc:
Interface for an Address Change set.  Objects that implements this interface track
 various change information on a set of addresses where the program has changed.

methods.javadoc: Returns the address set of all addresses where the listing has changed.
methods.name: getAddressSet
methods.comment: Returns the address set of all addresses where the listing has changed.

methods.javadoc:
Adds the address set to the set addresses where changes occurred.
@param addrSet the set of addresses to add as changes.
methods.name: add
methods.comment: Adds the address set to the set addresses where changes occurred.

params.name: addrSet
params.comment: the set of addresses to add as changes.

methods.name: addRange
methods.comment: Adds the range of addresses to the set addresses where changes occurred.

params.name: addr1
params.comment: the first address in the range

params.name: addr2
params.comment: the last address in the range. (inclusive)
